MER_RR__2P_flags|MERIS Level 2 Flag Codings
#
LAND             | 23      | Land product available
CLOUD            | 22      | Cloud product available
WATER            | 21      | Water product available
PCD_1_13         | 20      | Uncertain normalized surface reflectance
PCD_14           | 19      | Uncertain total water vapour content
PCD_15           | 18      | Uncertain algal pigment index 1 or cloud top pressure or top of atmosphere vegetation index
PCD_16           | 17      | Uncertain yellow substance and total suspended matter or rectified reflectances
PCD_17           | 16      | Uncertain algal pigment index 2 or bottom of atmosphere vegetation index
PCD_18           | 15      | Uncertain PAR or cloud albedo or land surface pressure
PCD_19           | 14      | Uncertain aerosol type and optical thickness or cloud optical thickness
COASTLINE        | 13      | Coastline pixel
COSMETIC         | 12      | Cosmetic pixel (from level-1b)
SUSPECT          | 11      | Suspect pixel (from level-1b)
OOADB            | 10      | Aerosol model is out of aerosol model database
ABSOA_DUST       |  9      | Dust-like absorbing aerosol selected for atmosphere correction
CASE2_S          |  8 & 21 | Turbid (sediment dominated Case 2) water
SNOW_ICE         |  8 & 23 | Snow/Ice covered land
CASE2_ANOM       |  7 & 21 | Anomalous scattering water
TOAVI_BRIGHT     |  7 & 23 | Bright pixel flagged by MGVI processing
CASE2_Y          |  6 & 21 | Yellow substance loaded water
TOAVI_BAD        |  6 & 23 | Bad pixel flagged by MGVI processing
